results.title: The Light That Failed
results.description: The X-Men have an all out battle with Mastermold and end up blasting him into the Siege Perilous (with Rogue in tow); Senator Kelly's wife dies.

results.title: Why Havok? Why Did You Kill Storm!?
The Cradle Will Fall
results.description: Longshot disappears in his own illusion; Nanny decides the X-Men need her help and a battle ensues as she tries to capture them for their own good; Havok blasts Nanny's ship and Storm is caught in the cross-fire.

results.title: The Dane Curse
results.description: The X-Men bury Storm; Polaris contacts Havok and asks him for help; The X-Men and Savage Land Mutates both arrive in Punta Arenas, Chile looking for Polaris; Mayhem ensues.

results.title: The Shattered Star
results.description: Zaladane steals Polaris' powers and frees her from Malice; Polaris gains size and super-strength in the transfer; The X-Men and Ka-Zar have an all out brawl with the Mutates.

results.title: Fever Dream
results.description: Wolverine is crucified by the Reavers and has a wild pain-induced hallucination; The remaining X-Men travel through the Siege Perilous to unknown futures; Wolvie pulls himself off the cross.

results.title: Where's Wolverine?
results.description: Wolvie and Jubilee play hide and seek with the Reavers while Wolvie recovers from his injuries.

results.title: Storm Warnings
results.description: Storm re-surfaces, alive and a young girl; Wolvie and Jubilee escape the Reavers and leave Australia; Magneto breaks his association with the X-Folk; Polaris is on a ship whose crew has gone crazy and Banshee comes to the rescue; Forge battles the Shadow King on the psychic plane; The Shadow King takes a new body; The Reavers decide to invade Muir Isle.

results.title: To Save The Dream--A New Legend Is Born!
All-New, All-Different--Here We Go Again
results.description: The Reavers invade Muir Isle and come up against an impromptu X-Men team; Freedom Force is called up to help out with the battle.

results.title: Crash and Burn
results.description: Freedom Force and Forge fight off the Reavers; Legion kills Destiny.

results.title: The Key That Breaks the Locke
results.description: The Mandarin conditions Psylocke to be his assassin; Psylocke takes a mind trip courtesy of Mojo where she kills her fellow X-Men and is re-made into an Asian with cybernetic eyes.

results.title: I Am Lady Mandarin
results.description: Wolvie and Jubilee arrive in Hong Kong just in time to run up against Lady Mandarin.

results.title: Broken Chains
results.description: Psylocke tries to condition Wolverine to serve The Hand and ends up breaking her own programming; The heroes head for home; Forge joins the Muir Island X-Men.

results.title: Dream a Little Dream
results.description: Colossus is living the life of a painter in Soho under the name of Peter Nicholas when he saves Phillip and Jenny from a pack of Magistrates who have been sent to bring them home; Guido finds Dazzler on the beach and tries to remind her of who she is; Masque makes Callisto a beautiful super-model.

results.title: Star 90
results.description: Dazzler's former agent who is obsessed with her moves in for the kill.

results.title: Harriers Hunt
results.description: Hardcase and the Harriers are hired to bring in Wolvie, Psylocke and Jubilee; Forge and Banshee continue their search for the X-Men; Jean arrives at the mansion and finds monsters.

results.title: Scary Monsters
results.description: Forge, Jean and Banshee fight monsters in the Morlock tunnels; Colossus has an art show and meets his mystery woman (Callisto); Jean and Sean monster out.

results.title: The Lower Depths
results.description: The X-Men fight off Masque and his deformed band and return to normal.

results.title: Hot Pursuit
results.description: The Magistrates invade X-Factor's ship to try and capture Jenny Ransome.

results.title: Storm at the Mercy of the Hounds !
Storm
results.description: The Shadow King gathers his hounds to hunt down Storm.

results.title: Gambit:  Out of the Frying Pan
results.description: Gambit helps Storm escape from the Shadow King.

results.title: There's A Storm On the Horizon!
Nanny:  Into the Fire
results.description: Gambit and Storm evade Nanny and the Shadow King; Gambit and Storm become a pair of thieves in New Orleans; Storm's adult memories are restored.

results.title: Madripoor Nights
results.description: Story cuts between a 1941 battle between Wolvie and Cap trying to save a young Natasha Romanoff from the clutches of Baron Strucker and Present Day where Wolvie, Cap, Black Widow and Psylocke face off against Strucker's children.

results.title: Rogue Redux
results.description: Rogue emerges from the Siege Perilous back to Australia and the arms of the Reavers; The Siege splits Rogue and Ms. Marvel into two beings; Rogue absorbes Gateway's powers and sends herself to the Savage  Land; Ms. Marvel ends up on Muir Isle where she is possessed by the Shadow King; Rogue and Ms. Marvel fight to the death in the Savage Land, but Magneto interferes; Maggie transports Ms. Marvel's powers back into Rogue (Whew!).

results.title: X-Tinction Agenda Part 1:  First Strike
results.description: The Magistrates (led by Havok) attack X-Mansion and kidnap Storm, Rahne, Boom-Boom and Warlock.

results.title: X-Tinction Agenda Part 4:  Flashpoint
results.description: Wolverine and Psylocke man an assault against Genosha to retrieve their captured team-mates; Storm is turned into a mutate.

results.title: X-Tinction Agenda Part 7: Capital Crimes
results.description: It's all out war in Genosha as the X-Men and the Magistrates try to stop Hodge's insane plans; Storm is restored to her adult body.

results.title: Follow Me X-Men--Or Professor X Dies!
Too Many Mutants
results.description: Forge, Jubilee, and Gambit officially join the X-Men; All the X-Folk wander around the mansion wondering what pattern the next phase of their lives should take.

results.title: Crossroads
results.description: Mags, Rogue, Fury and Ka-Zar begin their fight with Zaladane in the Savage Land; Lila teleports the X-Men to Deathbird's lair where they are trapped.

results.title: The Path Not Taken
results.description: The X-Men help Xavier and Lilandra overthrow Deathbird, but things aren't always what they seem; Magneto is captured by Zaladane and she attempts to steal his powers; Rogue, Ka-Zar and Fury come to the rescue; Magneto kills Zaladane.

results.title: Double Death
results.description: Lila spirits most of the X-Men and Deathbird away from Lilandra's clutches; Wolvie kills Xavier, but another takes his place; The Starjammers are sent to kill the X-Men; The plot is revealed--It's always the flamin' Skrulls isn't it.

results.title: Free Charley
results.description: It's an all out space battle between the X-Men and the War Skrulls; Xavier and the X-Men return to Earth.

results.title: The Muir Island Saga: In the Grip of the Shadow King
The Battle of Muir Isle
results.description: The X-Men return to earth and attempt to invade Muir Isle whose inhabitants have all been taken over by the Shadow King.

results.title: The Muir Island Saga: Colossus is Back
Bad To the Bone
results.description: The Shadow King sends Colossus to kill Xavier and Stevie, but the Prof restores his real memories and breaks the psychic hold; The X-Men, also under the Shadow King's influence, battle each other on Muir Isle.

results.title: The Muir Island Saga: Pyrrhic Victory!
One Step Back--Two Steps Forward
results.description: It is a final battle royale between the X-Men and the Shadow King; Legion slips into a coma after he is freed from the Shadow King's influence; Xavier loses the use of his legs (again).

results.title: Fresh Upstart
results.description: X-Men Gold Team is formed (X-Men Blue appear in the new X-Men #1); Trevor Fitzroy of the Upstarts sends Sentinels to slaughter Donald Pierce and the Reavers as well as the White Queen and the Hellions (and doesn't do a shabby job of taking out both).

results.title: Payback
results.description: The X-Men track the White Queen, who is being possessed by Jean Grey, to Fitzroy's stonghold where she is being held captive; Fitzroy kills all of the Hellions to open a portal from his future where a band of bad guys pour through; Followed closely by Bishop, Randall, and Malcom (X-Men from the future).

results.title: Bishop's Crossing
results.description: Bishop battles the X-Men, believing them to be imposters, and Fitzroy escapes in the struggle.

results.title: Into the Void
results.description: Sunfire and the X-Men open a portal to another dimension; Bishop continues to track down criminals from his own time.

results.title: Down the Rabbit Hole
results.description: The X-Men fall through the portal to another dimension where they run across Colossus' long-dead brother.

results.title: Close Call
results.description: Mikhail closes the portal and he and the X-Men return to Earth.

results.title: Bishop To King's Five
results.description: The X-Men punk out Bishop and he has a long dream about the events in his future that led to him jumping to the present; Bishop joins the X-Men.

results.title: Time and Place
results.description: Bishop struggles to cope with his new team and his new time.

results.title: Knots
results.description: Bobby takes Opal to meet his parents; Mystique ticks Archangel off big time; Forge asks Storm to marry him.

results.title: Frayed
results.description: Iceman and Hiro fight off the Cyburai who have interrupted Bobby's date (but Hiro gives his life for victory); Forge leaves the X-Men before hearing Storm's answer to his proposal.

results.title: Underbelly
results.description: Callisto seeks out the X-Men for help as she is being chased down by the blood-thirsty Morlocks; Cal reverts to her old ugly self.

results.title: The Morlocks Take Manhattan
results.description: Callisto and Mikhail reveal their duplicity; The X-Men battle the Morlocks; Mikhail unlocks Iceman's full genetic potential.

results.title: The Last Morlock Story
results.description: Mikhail becomes the new leader of the Morlocks and leads them right to their apparent deaths.

results.title: Overture
results.description: The Horsemen attack the X-Men; During a speech in Central Park, Cable (or someone who looks exactly like Cable) shoots Professor X down in cold blood.

results.title: Familiar Refrain
results.description: Half of the X-Men try to track down Cable and Stryfe while the other half gets busted up by Apocalypse; Cable runs into Wolvie and Bishop at Department K in Canada.

results.title: Crescendo
results.description: Scott and Jean must choose between saving the life of a child or taking down Stryfe and the Dark Riders.
